Bleach Manufacturing Prevention Program:  Accident prevention is achieved through safe handling procedures and safety systems that properly protect chlorine during receipt, storage and use.  This starts with DOT FRA approved 90-ton railcars that are robustly designed to contain chlorine through expected conditions during transport, storage and unloading.  It continues through having employees trained in proper handling procedures and equipping them with equipment to safely transfer chemicals during manufacture.  



Hawkins accident prevention program includes:

1. Procedures and training for handling chlorine during manufacturing of sodium hypochlorite;

2. Implement safety systems to manage risks identified during process hazard analysis;

3. Conduct necessary plant maintenance and inspections to ensure equipment is in good working order;

4. Vendor provided DOT approved railcars;

5. Adhere to OSHA workplace safety regulations;

6. Follow Chlorine Institute standards.

7. Members in good standings with National Association of Chemical Distributors
